 and ultimately more productive model for change-a model Galvan calls "institutional syncretism."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aAcculturationxCase studiesxSenegal. 0aLand tenurexHistoryxSenegalxSine-Saloum. 0aSerer (African people)xGovernment relations. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520929425423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520929425.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles